# Relatos de Papel Cursor Rules

- Start from the nearest concrete file before changing anything.
- Keep the current Vite + React 19 + TypeScript + MUI architecture stable.
- Use functional components only.
- Use explicit TypeScript, typed mock data, and real custom hooks.
- Avoid `any`, `console.log`, dead code, and unused exports.
- Do not invent backend calls inside the frontend layer.
- Do not move route declarations out of `src/App.tsx`.
- Do not hardcode brand colors outside the theme.
- Do not create new global CSS unless the style is truly global.
- Reuse existing components, barrels, and theme tokens before creating new files.
- At the end of every AI-driven iteration, update [.github/copilot-instructions.md](.github/copilot-instructions.md), [.cursorrules](.cursorrules), [README.md](README.md), and [prompts.md](prompts.md) so the shared context and the user-facing guide stay synchronized.

## Scope map

### Root files

- `package.json`, `package-lock.json`, `vite.config.ts`, `eslint.config.js`, `tsconfig.json`, `tsconfig.app.json`, and `tsconfig.node.json` control build, lint, and TypeScript behavior.
- `index.html` is the app entry shell.
- `README.md` documents scripts, CI, and delivery expectations.
- `models.md` is the canonical domain model reference.
- `prompts.md` stores reusable prompts and AI context.
- `.env.example` is reserved for future environment variables only.
- `vercel.json` configures SPA fallback routing for Vercel deployments.

### .github

- `.github/workflows/ci.yml` currently enforces lint and format checks.
- `.github/copilot-instructions.md` is the always-on workspace guidance.

Future `.github` folders:

- `.github/instructions/` for file-scoped rules.
- `.github/prompts/` for reusable prompts.
- `.github/agents/` for specialized workflows.
- `.github/skills/` for repeatable tool-driven tasks.
- more workflows only if they support CI, preview deploys, or release automation.

### src/App.tsx

- This is the single source of truth for routes.
- Providers wrap routes in this order: `ThemeProvider` → `BrowserRouter` → `AuthProvider` → `ShoppingCartProvider` → `AlertProvider` → `Routes`.
- `ProtectedRoute` guards `/checkout` and `/profile`.
- `/login` is outside `MainLayout` (no navbar/footer).
- Keep public routes, protected routes, and fallback routes here.

### src/root.tsx

- Bootstrap only.
- Import fonts, global CSS, StrictMode, and mount `App`.
- Keep business logic out of this file.

### src/root.css

- Global app styles only.
- Use it for resets, body background, and other truly global app-shell styles.
- Prefer MUI theme overrides for everything else.

### src/config/mui/

- `palette.ts` holds the brand colors only.
- `typography.ts` holds the Inter and Caveat stacks.
- `theme.ts` wires the palette, typography, shape, and component overrides.
- `index.ts` is the barrel export.

Future scope:

- add component overrides or theme tokens here when they are shared.
- never duplicate brand values in pages when they already belong in the theme.

### src/config/navigation/navigation.config.ts

- `ROUTES` holds all route path constants.
- `CATALOG_PARAMS` holds all URL query-param keys for catalog filters.
- `buildCatalogUrl(opts)` builds a typed catalog URL from optional filter options.
- `NAVIGATION_QUERY_PARAMS` holds `redirect` param key for auth redirects.
- Never scatter URL string literals across pages; always use these constants.

### src/layouts/main/

- `Main.layout.tsx` owns the shell and `Outlet`.
- `Navbar/Navbar.tsx` owns the sticky header and navigation affordances.
- `Footer.tsx` owns the footer and brand closure.
- `Navbar/components/catalog-action/` owns the expandable inline search widget.
- `Navbar/components/auth-action/` owns the login/profile icon and menu.
- `Navbar/components/shopping-cart-action/` owns the cart badge and opens the drawer.
- `index.ts` should expose the layout entry point.

### src/components/ui/

- `BrandIcon.tsx` is the brand mark; accepts a `variant` prop (`'primary'` | `'secondary'`).
- `Button.tsx` is a placeholder; replace with a real typed wrapper or use MUI Button directly.
- `Examples.tsx` is the UI showcase, not production logic.
- `CustomerAvatar.tsx` is a reusable avatar for customer display.
- `index.ts` is the barrel export.

### src/components/book/

- `BookCard.tsx` is the book preview card used by catalog and related-books grid; reads from `useShoppingCart`.
- `BookCardSkeleton.tsx` is the loading placeholder matching `BookCard` layout.
- `book-image.tsx` renders a cover image with a seeded-color fallback when the URL is missing or broken.
- `index.ts` is the barrel export.

### src/components/catalog/

- `CatalogFilters.tsx` owns the filter panel: title/author search, category, format, language, price range slider, and clear button.
- `CatalogToolbar.tsx` owns the results count label and sort-by/sort-order controls.
- `index.ts` exports components and their public types (`CatalogFiltersValues`, `CatalogSortBy`, `CatalogSortOrder`).

### src/components/checkout/

- `checkout-order-summary.tsx` shows the cart items, total, and pay/go-to-catalog buttons.
- `checkout-address-picker.tsx` lets the user choose a shipping address.
- `checkout-empty.tsx` renders the empty-cart state for the checkout page.
- `index.ts` is the barrel export.

### src/components/shopping-cart/

- `shopping-cart-drawer.tsx` is the slide-in cart panel opened from the navbar.
- `shopping-cart-content.tsx` composes the drawer body.
- `shopping-cart-item.tsx` renders a single cart row with `QuantityInput` and remove button.
- `shopping-cart-list.tsx` lists all cart items.
- `shopping-cart-empty.tsx` renders the empty-cart CTA.
- `index.ts` is the barrel export.

### src/components/inputs/

- `quantity-input.tsx` is a reusable +/− quantity stepper; used in `BookCard`, `ShoppingCartItem`, and `Book.page.tsx`.

### src/components/profile/

- `profile.tsx` is the top-level profile composite component.
- `profile-layout.tsx` wraps sections in a consistent layout.
- `profile-header/ProfileHeader.tsx` shows the customer avatar and name.
- `profile-item-card.tsx` is the card shell for profile sections.
- `profile-logout-button.tsx` triggers logout from context.
- `sections/profile-form-section.tsx` lets the user update personal data.
- `sections/profile-address-section.tsx` manages customer addresses.
- `sections/profile-orders-section/` contains the order list and order card components.
- `index.ts` is the barrel export.

### src/components/address/

- `address-card.tsx`, `address-form.tsx`, `address-list.tsx`, `add-address-modal.tsx` handle address CRUD UI.
- `index.ts` is the barrel export.

### src/components/auth/

- `ProtectedRoute.tsx` redirects unauthenticated users to `/login?redirect=<current-path>`.
- `index.ts` is the barrel export.

### src/context/

- `auth/Auth.context.tsx` + `Auth.provider.tsx` — auth state, login, logout, and user.
- `shopping-cart/shopping-cart.context.tsx` + `shopping-cart.provider.tsx` — cart state backed by `useShoppingCartState`.
- `alert/alert.context.tsx` + `alert.provider.tsx` — snackbar/toast notification system.
- `index.ts` is the barrel export.

### src/hooks/

- `auth/use-auth.hook.ts` — consumes `AuthContext`; exposes `user`, `login`, `logout`, `isAuthenticated`.
- `shopping-cart/use-shopping-cart-state.hook.ts` — owns cart state, `addItem`, `removeItem`, `updateQuantity`, `clearCart`, and localStorage sync.
- `shopping-cart/use-shopping-cart.hook.ts` — consumes `ShoppingCartContext`.
- `customer/use-customer-state.hook.ts` — customer data fetch and update logic.
- `address/use-address-state.hook.tsx` — address list, create, and delete logic.
- `alert/use-alert.hook.ts` — exposes `showAlert(message, severity)`.
- `catalog/use-catalog-search-params.hook.ts` — reads and writes all catalog filter/sort/page state to the URL via `useSearchParams`; depends on `BookFiltersMetadata` for price-range defaults.
- `api/use-api.hook.ts` — incomplete placeholder; retire or implement.
- `index.ts` is the barrel export.

### src/pages/

- Page files must stay thin and compose reusable components.
- `landing/Landing.page.tsx` — public entry page.
- `login/Login.page.tsx` — login form; success redirects to `profile` (or `redirect` param).
- `catalog/Catalog.page.tsx` — full catalog with filters, sort, pagination, skeleton loaders, and debounced search. All filter/sort/page state lives in the URL.
- `book/Book.page.tsx` — book detail, related books grid, stock status, and the only place where a book can be added to the cart with a quantity picker.
- `checkout/Checkout.page.tsx` — protected; address picker + order summary; on success calls `window.alert`, clears cart, navigates to `/`.
- `profile/Profile.page.tsx` — protected; shows profile header, form, addresses, and last orders.
- `not-found/NotFound.page.tsx` — 404 fallback with back-to-catalog CTA.
- `story-book/StoryBook.page.tsx` — UI component showcase.
- `index.ts` is the page barrel export.

### src/types/

- `book.types.ts` — `Book`, `BookCategory`, `BookFormat`.
- `customer.types.ts` — `Customer`.
- `order.types.ts` — `Order`, `OrderStatus`.
- `order-item.types.ts` — `OrderItem`.
- `cart.types.ts` — `Cart` (keyed by `book.id`), `CartItem`.
- `category.types.ts` — `Category`.
- `tag.types.ts` — `Tag`.
- `picture.types.ts` — `Picture`.
- `index.ts` — shared export surface.

### src/services/

- `api/apiClient.ts` — centralized `fetch` wrapper with `Authorization: Bearer` header injection and single-retry on `401`.
- `config.ts` — exports `USE_MOCK` and `API_URL` derived from Vite env vars.
- `books/books.service.ts` — list, detail, featured, related, search, filters metadata, and CRUD.
- `customers/customers.service.ts` — CRUD, login, register, password change, email check.
- `orders/orders.service.ts` — list, detail, create, update, cancel, stats, purchase check.
- `addresses/addresses.service.ts` — list and CRUD by `customerId`.
- `http.ts` and `index.ts` — compatibility re-exports.
- `types.ts` — service-layer types including `BookFiltersMetadata`, `PaginatedResponse`, etc.

### src/mocks/

- `books.mock.ts` — large catalog generated from Open Library, with covers, categories, format, year, price, stock, rating, and review count.
- `customer.mock.ts` — test users.
- `orders.mock.ts` — sample orders with status.
- `addresses.mock.ts` — addresses grouped by `customerId`.
- `shopping-cart.mock.ts` — initial cart fixture for dev/testing.

### src/utils/

- `price.utils.ts` — `formatPrice(amount)` using `Intl.NumberFormat` (USD).
- `shopping-cart.utils.ts` — `readStoredCart`, `writeStoredCart`, `clearStoredCart` for localStorage persistence under key `relatos-de-papel.cart`.

## Page contract

- Landing is public.
- Login must redirect to profile after success (or to `?redirect=` param if present).
- Catalog filters by title and author; supports category, format, language, and price range; all state in URL.
- Only the book detail view may add a book to the cart.
- Cart must remain visible (navbar badge + drawer) on catalog and book views.
- Checkout is protected; on success must call `window.alert`, clear the cart, then navigate to `/`.
- Profile is protected and must show user data plus last orders.
- NotFound must return the user to the app.
- StoryBook is for visual verification only.

## Styling contract

- Keep the current brand palette: navy primary `#1B1F3A`, warm sand secondary `#D9A77D`, white contrast.
- Keep Inter for body text and Caveat for headings.
- Prefer MUI components, `sx`, and theme overrides over ad hoc CSS.
- Keep `src/root.css` for only global resets or truly global app-shell styling.
- Avoid generic default MUI screens; the app should feel book-themed, warm, and polished.
- If a reusable visual pattern appears more than once, promote it into `src/components/ui` or a domain component folder.

## Data and integration rules

- Use typed mock data until a backend exists.
- Do not add HTTP calls into pages as a shortcut.
- If network integration arrives later, create a dedicated `src/services/` or `src/api/` layer and keep pages thin.
- Keep search/filter logic client-side until the assignment changes.
- Cart state is persisted in `localStorage` under `relatos-de-papel.cart` and synced across tabs via the `storage` event.
- When regenerating the book catalog, use Open Library Search and Covers APIs in batch, cache the result, and persist the snapshot in `src/mocks/books.mock.ts`. Do not fetch from pages at runtime.

## Quality and validation

- Respect ESLint and Prettier; CI fails when lint or format fails.
- Avoid `any`, `console.log`, dead code, and unused exports.
- Keep components focused and easy to read.
- Update barrels when new modules are added.
- Validate the touched slice with the narrowest useful check before widening scope.
- If a change touches a shared contract, update every consumer of that contract.
- Avoid synchronous `setState` directly inside `useEffect`; derive state or update via async callbacks.
